---
description:
Defines the Design Token Architecture for the LexMastery Design System.

alwaysApply: true
---

# Token Architecture

LexMastery follows a four-layer Design Token system.

Never use raw values inside widgets.

Every visual value must originate from Design Tokens.

---

# Token Hierarchy

Primitive Tokens

↓

Semantic Tokens

↓

Component Tokens

↓

Feature Tokens

Never skip layers.

---

# Primitive Tokens

Primitive Tokens are raw design values.

They never describe meaning.

Examples:

Blue 500

Gray 100

16 px

8 px

24 px

Font Weight 700

Duration 200 ms

Primitive tokens are never used directly inside widgets.

---

# Semantic Tokens

Semantic Tokens describe purpose.

Examples:

color.background.primary

color.background.secondary

color.surface.primary

color.surface.elevated

color.text.primary

color.text.secondary

color.text.inverse

color.border.default

color.border.focus

color.success

color.warning

color.error

spacing.xs

spacing.sm

spacing.md

spacing.lg

spacing.xl

radius.sm

radius.md

radius.lg

radius.xl

elevation.card

motion.fast

motion.normal

motion.slow

Widgets consume Semantic Tokens.

Never consume Primitive Tokens.

---

# Component Tokens

Component Tokens specialize semantic tokens for reusable UI.

Examples:

button.primary.background

button.primary.foreground

button.primary.padding

button.primary.radius

button.secondary.background

textfield.background

textfield.border

textfield.focus

textfield.padding

card.background

card.radius

card.padding

dialog.background

dialog.radius

navigation.background

navigation.icon.active

navigation.icon.inactive

Only reusable components may own Component Tokens.

---

# Feature Tokens

Feature Tokens belong to a business capability.

Examples:

quiz.correct.background

quiz.correct.border

quiz.incorrect.background

quiz.progress.indicator

flashcard.front.background

flashcard.back.background

flashcard.shadow

diagnostic.score.high

diagnostic.score.medium

diagnostic.score.low

study.streak.active

study.streak.inactive

ai.message.user.background

ai.message.assistant.background

ai.message.system.background

course.completed.badge

course.locked.overlay

Feature Tokens must never be reused across unrelated features.

---

# Theme Resolution

Theme lookup order:

Feature Token

↓

Component Token

↓

Semantic Token

↓

Primitive Token

Never bypass this chain.

---

# Dark Mode

Dark Mode overrides Semantic Tokens.

Primitive Tokens remain unchanged.

Component Tokens inherit automatically.

Feature Tokens inherit automatically unless explicitly overridden.

---

# Accessibility Themes

Accessibility themes modify Semantic Tokens.

Examples:

High Contrast

Reduced Motion

Large Text

Institution Theme

Color Blind Theme

Do not modify components directly.

---

# White Label Support

Future institution branding must only override

Primitive Tokens

or

Semantic Tokens.

Never duplicate components.

---

# Token Naming

Use dot notation.

Good:

color.text.primary

button.primary.background

quiz.correct.background

Bad:

blueColor

primaryBlue

buttonColor

textColor

---

# Token Storage

Tokens should exist as strongly typed Dart classes.

Never store tokens as arbitrary maps.

Avoid string lookups.

Use compile-time safety wherever possible.

---

# Theme Extensions

Expose tokens through Theme Extensions.

Widgets should access tokens through BuildContext extensions.

Example:

context.tokens.color.text.primary

Never access raw Color values.

---

# Hardcoded Values

Forbidden inside widgets:

Color()

EdgeInsets.all(16)

SizedBox(height: 24)

BorderRadius.circular(12)

Duration(milliseconds: 200)

TextStyle(fontSize: 16)

Always reference tokens.

---

# Cursor Instructions

Whenever generating UI:

Never hardcode visual values.

Always consume Design Tokens.

Always resolve through Theme Extensions.

If a required token does not exist,

create the token,

not a hardcoded value.